replies.body:
His Q should knock aside all units hit, with the shockwave of its passage leaving a furrow in the earth that blocks enemy pathing. Allies can cross the furrow on a rainbow bridge.

His W should extend its remaining duration by 1 second (up to its original duration) and increase the AS boost by 5% with every autoattack. It should also ignore the attack speed cap because.

His E should be a PBAoE with a radius of... oh, I dunno, maybe 300 units. And no cast time; that part sucks. Also, add a decaying 50% movement speed boost. Increase the cost by 10 health per rank, though, so he can't spam it.

His R should additionally cause him to grow by 2000 units, with movement speed and attack range increasing to match, and also set the surrounding area (Runeterra, that is) on fire. The 6-second duration is just fine. After it ends, Olaf dies. And so does everyone else. On both teams. And then there's a flood. Hey, it's called Ragnar√∂k, don't blame me.

